{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"This is the first of two\nrather extraordinary photographs"},{"time":3301,"text":"I'm going to show you today."},{"time":4675,"text":"It was taken 18 years ago."},{"time":6277,"text":"I was 19 years old at the time."},{"time":7802,"text":"I had just returned"},{"time":8977,"text":"from one of the deepest dives\nI'd ever made at that time --"},{"time":11787,"text":"a little over 200 feet."},{"time":12969,"text":"And I had caught this little fish."},{"time":14938,"text":"It turns out that particular one\nwas the first of its kind"},{"time":17732,"text":"ever taken alive."},{"time":18910,"text":"I'm not just an ichthyologist,\nI'm a bona fide fish nerd."},{"time":21608,"text":"And to a fish nerd,\nthis is some pretty exciting stuff."},{"time":24329,"text":"More exciting was the fact\nthat the person who took this photo"},{"time":27274,"text":"is a guy named Jack Randall,"},{"time":28634,"text":"the greatest living\nichthyologist on earth --"},{"time":31441,"text":"the Grand Poobah\nof fish nerds, if you will."},{"time":34005,"text":"And so, it was really exciting\nto me to have this moment in time."},{"time":38931,"text":"It set the course for the rest of my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41055,"text":"But really, the most significant,\nmost profound thing about this picture"},{"time":44526,"text":"is it was taken two days\nbefore I was completely paralyzed"},{"time":47289,"text":"from the neck down."},{"time":48475,"text":"I made a really stupid kind of mistake"},{"time":50848,"text":"that most 19-year-old males do\nwhen they think they're immortal,"},{"time":53912,"text":"and I got a bad case of the bends\nand was paralyzed,"},{"time":56507,"text":"and had to be flown back for treatment."},{"time":60156,"text":"I learned two really\nimportant things that day."},{"time":62630,"text":"The first thing I learned -- well,\nI'm mortal. That's a really big one."},{"time":66044,"text":"And the second thing I learned\nwas that I knew, with profound certainty,"},{"time":69517,"text":"that this is exactly what I was going\nto do for the rest of my life."},{"time":72781,"text":"I had to focus all my energies"},{"time":74433,"text":"towards going to find\nnew species of things"},{"time":77576,"text":"down on deep coral reefs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79348,"text":"When you think of a coral reef,\nthis is what most people think of:"},{"time":82489,"text":"these big, hard, elaborate corals,"},{"time":84283,"text":"lots of bright, colorful\nfishes and things."},{"time":86326,"text":"But this is really\njust the tip of the iceberg."},{"time":88556,"text":"If you look at this diagram\nof a coral reef,"},{"time":90671,"text":"we know a lot about that part\nup near the top."},{"time":92845,"text":"The reason we know so much about it"},{"time":95200,"text":"is scuba divers can very easily\ngo down there and access it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98064,"text":"There is a problem with scuba, though,"},{"time":100200,"text":"in that it imposes some limitations\non how deep you can go."},{"time":102992,"text":"It turns out that depth is about 200 feet."},{"time":105031,"text":"I'll get into why that is\nin just a minute,"},{"time":107372,"text":"but the point is, scuba divers\ngenerally stay less than 100 feet deep,"},{"time":110922,"text":"and very rarely go much below this,\nat least, not with any kind of sanity."},{"time":114470,"text":"So to go deeper, most biologists\nhave turned to submersibles."},{"time":118026,"text":"Now, submersibles are great,\nwonderful things,"},{"time":120200,"text":"but if you're going to spend 30,000\ndollars a day to use one of these things"},{"time":123879,"text":"and it's capable of going 2,000 feet,"},{"time":125697,"text":"you're not going to go farting around\nup here in a couple of hundred feet,"},{"time":129200,"text":"you're going to go way down deep."},{"time":130998,"text":"So the bottom line is, almost\nall research using submersibles"},{"time":133891,"text":"has taken place well below 500 feet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135655,"text":"Now, it's pretty obvious at this point"},{"time":137501,"text":"there's a zone here in the middle."},{"time":139153,"text":"That's the zone"},{"time":140448,"text":"that centers around my own\npersonal pursuit of happiness."},{"time":143178,"text":"I want to find out what's in this zone;\nwe know almost nothing about it."},{"time":146600,"text":"Scuba divers can't get there,\nsubmarines go right on past it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149601,"text":"It took me a year to learn to walk again\nafter my diving accident in Palau."},{"time":153172,"text":"During that year,"},{"time":154347,"text":"I spent a lot of time learning\nabout the physics and physiology of diving"},{"time":157810,"text":"and how to overcome these limitations."},{"time":159647,"text":"I'm just going to show you a basic idea."},{"time":161593,"text":"We're all breathing air right now."},{"time":163248,"text":"Air is a mixture of oxygen and nitrogen,"},{"time":165184,"text":"20 percent oxygen, 80 percent nitrogen."},{"time":167287,"text":"It's in our lungs."},{"time":168461,"text":"And there's a phenomenon\ncalled Henry's law,"},{"time":170549,"text":"that says gases will dissolve into a fluid"},{"time":172579,"text":"in proportion to the partial pressures\nyou're exposing them to."},{"time":175577,"text":"So, basically the gas\ndissolves into our body."},{"time":177760,"text":"The oxygen is bound by metabolism,\nwe use it for energy."},{"time":180412,"text":"The nitrogen sort of floats around\nin our blood and tissues."},{"time":183257,"text":"That's fine, it's how we're designed."},{"time":185200,"text":"The problem happens\nwhen you go underwater."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187235,"text":"The deeper you go underwater,\nthe higher the pressure is."},{"time":190062,"text":"If you were to go down\nto a depth of about 130 feet,"},{"time":192627,"text":"which is the recommended\nlimit for most scuba divers,"},{"time":195176,"text":"you'd get this pressure effect."},{"time":196698,"text":"The effect of that pressure is you have\nan increased density of gas molecules"},{"time":200405,"text":"in every breath you take."},{"time":201645,"text":"Over time, those gas molecules\ndissolve into your blood and tissues"},{"time":205508,"text":"and start to fill you up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206945,"text":"Now, if you were to go\ndown to, say, 300 feet,"},{"time":209612,"text":"you don't have five times as many\ngas molecules in your lungs,"},{"time":212574,"text":"you've got 10 times as many\ngas molecules in your lungs."},{"time":215226,"text":"And, sure enough, they dissolve\ninto your blood and tissues as well."},{"time":218531,"text":"And if you were to go down to where\nthere's 15 times as much --"},{"time":221636,"text":"the deeper you go, the more\nexacerbating the problem becomes."},{"time":224669,"text":"The limitation of diving with air\nis all those dots in your body,"},{"time":229182,"text":"all the nitrogen and all the oxygen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230975,"text":"There are three basic\nlimitations of scuba diving."},{"time":233699,"text":"The first limitation is the oxygen --"},{"time":235558,"text":"oxygen toxicity."},{"time":236909,"text":"Now, we all know the song:\n\"Love is like oxygen."},{"time":239187,"text":"You get too much, you get too high.\nNot enough, and you're gonna die.\""},{"time":242506,"text":"Well, in the context of diving,\nyou get too much, you die also."},{"time":245518,"text":"You die because oxygen\ntoxicity can cause a seizure."},{"time":248542,"text":"It makes you convulse underwater --\nnot a good thing to happen underwater."},{"time":252114,"text":"It happens because there's too much\nconcentration of oxygen in your body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255645,"text":"The nitrogen has two problems."},{"time":257311,"text":"One of them is what Jacques Cousteau\ncalled \"rapture of the deep.\""},{"time":261708,"text":"It's nitrogen narcosis."},{"time":263074,"text":"It makes you loopy; the deeper\nyou go, the loopier you get."},{"time":265885,"text":"You don't want to drive drunk,\nyou don't want to dive drunk."},{"time":268778,"text":"So that's a real big problem."},{"time":270200,"text":"And of course, the third problem"},{"time":271767,"text":"is the one I found out\nthe hard way in Palau,"},{"time":273934,"text":"which is the bends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275116,"text":"One thing I forgot to mention"},{"time":276531,"text":"is that to obviate the problem\nof nitrogen narcosis --"},{"time":279088,"text":"all of those blue dots in our body --"},{"time":280898,"text":"you remove the nitrogen\nand replace it with helium."},{"time":283322,"text":"Helium's a gas; there're a lot\nof reasons why helium's good,"},{"time":286179,"text":"it's a tiny molecule, it's inert,\nit doesn't give you narcosis."},{"time":289190,"text":"So that's the basic concept we use."},{"time":290916,"text":"But the theory's relatively easy."},{"time":292519,"text":"The tricky part is the implementation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294376,"text":"So this is how I began about 15 years ago."},{"time":296509,"text":"I'll admit, it wasn't exactly\nthe smartest of starts,"},{"time":299239,"text":"but you've got to start somewhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300929,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":301961,"text":"At the time, I wasn't the only one\nwho didn't know what I was doing."},{"time":305183,"text":"Almost nobody did."},{"time":306366,"text":"This rig was actually used\nfor a dive of 300 feet."},{"time":308730,"text":"But over time we got better at it,"},{"time":310389,"text":"and we came up with this really\nsophisticated-looking rig"},{"time":313105,"text":"with four scuba tanks, five regulators\nand all the right gas mixtures,"},{"time":316436,"text":"all that good stuff."},{"time":317611,"text":"It was fine and dandy, it allowed us\nto go down and find new species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320912,"text":"This picture was taken at 300 feet,\ncatching new species of fish."},{"time":323988,"text":"The problem was\nit didn't allow us much time."},{"time":326115,"text":"For all its bulk and size, it only gave us\nabout 15 minutes at most"},{"time":329341,"text":"down at those sorts of depths."},{"time":330877,"text":"We needed more time.\nThere had to be a better way."},{"time":333238,"text":"And indeed, there is a better way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334936,"text":"In 1994, I was fortunate\nenough to get access"},{"time":337120,"text":"to these prototype\nclosed-circuit rebreathers."},{"time":340527,"text":"Closed-circuit rebreather:\nwhat makes it different from scuba,"},{"time":343568,"text":"and why is it better?"},{"time":344753,"text":"Well, there are three main\nadvantages to a rebreather."},{"time":347628,"text":"One, they're quiet,\nthey don't make any noise."},{"time":349812,"text":"Two, they allow you to stay\nunderwater longer."},{"time":352001,"text":"Three, they allow you to go deeper."},{"time":353898,"text":"How is it that they do that?"},{"time":355279,"text":"In order to really understand\nhow they do that,"},{"time":357510,"text":"you have to look underneath the hood\nand see what's going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360423,"text":"There are three basic systems\nto a closed-circuit rebreather."},{"time":363318,"text":"The most fundamental\nis called the breathing loop."},{"time":365930,"text":"It's a breathing loop\nbecause you breathe off of it;"},{"time":368396,"text":"it's a closed loop, and you breathe\nthe same gas around and around."},{"time":371577,"text":"There's a mouthpiece\nthat you put in your mouth,"},{"time":373945,"text":"and there's a counter lung,\nor in this case, two counter lungs."},{"time":376994,"text":"The counter lungs aren't high tech,\nthey're simply flexible bags."},{"time":380082,"text":"They allow you to mechanically\nbreathe, mechanically ventilate."},{"time":383083,"text":"When you exhale, it goes\nin the exhale counter lung;"},{"time":385558,"text":"when you inhale, it comes\nfrom the inhale counter lung."},{"time":388167,"text":"It's just pure mechanics, allowing you\nto cycle air through this breathing loop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391976,"text":"The other component on a breathing loop\nis the carbon-dioxide-absorbent canister."},{"time":396204,"text":"Now, as we breathe,\nwe produce carbon dioxide,"},{"time":399100,"text":"and that carbon dioxide needs\nto be scrubbed out of the system."},{"time":402125,"text":"There's a chemical filter in there"},{"time":403797,"text":"that pulls the carbon dioxide\nout of the breathing gas,"},{"time":406402,"text":"so that when it comes back to us,\nit's safe to breathe again."},{"time":409814,"text":"That's the breathing loop in a nutshell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412056,"text":"The second main component\nof a closed-circuit rebreather"},{"time":415024,"text":"is the gas system."},{"time":416390,"text":"The primary purpose of the gas system\nis to provide oxygen,"},{"time":419864,"text":"to replenish the oxygen\nthat your body consumes."},{"time":422504,"text":"So the main tank, the main critical thing,"},{"time":424619,"text":"is this oxygen gas\nsupply cylinder we have here."},{"time":427484,"text":"But if we only had\nan oxygen gas supply cylinder,"},{"time":429865,"text":"we wouldn't be able to go very deep,"},{"time":431605,"text":"because we'd run into\noxygen toxicity very quickly."},{"time":434054,"text":"So we need another gas,\nsomething to dilute the oxygen with."},{"time":437200,"text":"And that, fittingly enough,\nis called the diluent gas supply."},{"time":440486,"text":"In our applications, we generally\nput air inside this diluent gas supply,"},{"time":444946,"text":"because it's a very cheap\nand easy source of nitrogen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447670,"text":"So that's where we get our nitrogen from."},{"time":449671,"text":"But if we want to go deeper,\nof course, we need another gas supply,"},{"time":453164,"text":"and helium is what\nwe really need to go deep."},{"time":455299,"text":"Usually we'll have\na slightly larger cylinder,"},{"time":457471,"text":"mounted exterior\non the rebreather, like this."},{"time":459662,"text":"That's what we use to inject,\nas we start to do our deep dives."},{"time":462709,"text":"We also have a second oxygen cylinder,\nsolely as a backup;"},{"time":465899,"text":"if there's a problem\nwith our first oxygen supply,"},{"time":468262,"text":"we can continue to breathe."},{"time":469595,"text":"The way you manage all these different\ngases and different gas supplies"},{"time":473080,"text":"is this really high-tech, sophisticated\ngas block up on the front here,"},{"time":476495,"text":"where it's easy to reach."},{"time":477727,"text":"It's got the valves and knobs\nand things you need"},{"time":480043,"text":"to inject the right gases\nat the right time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482126,"text":"Normally, you don't have to do that,"},{"time":483869,"text":"because all of it's done automatically"},{"time":485706,"text":"with the electronics,\nthe third system of a rebreather."},{"time":488358,"text":"The most critical part of a rebreather\nare the oxygen sensors."},{"time":491307,"text":"You need three, so if one goes bad,\nyou know which one it is."},{"time":494197,"text":"You need voting logic."},{"time":495375,"text":"You also have three microprocessors."},{"time":497304,"text":"Any one of those computers\ncan run the entire system,"},{"time":499808,"text":"so if you have to lose two of them,"},{"time":501510,"text":"there's back-up power supplies."},{"time":503026,"text":"And there are multiple displays,\nto get the information to the diver."},{"time":506323,"text":"This is the high-tech gadgetry\nthat allows us to do what we do"},{"time":509839,"text":"on these deep dives."},{"time":511097,"text":"I can talk about it all day --\njust ask my wife --"},{"time":513528,"text":"but I want to move on\nto something much more interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516231,"text":"I'm going to take you on a deep dive,"},{"time":518021,"text":"and show you what it's like to do one."},{"time":519856,"text":"We start up on the boat,"},{"time":521031,"text":"For all this high-tech,\nexpensive equipment,"},{"time":523160,"text":"this is still the best way\nto get in the water,"},{"time":525393,"text":"just flop over the side of the boat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527156,"text":"Now, as I showed you\nin the earlier diagram,"},{"time":529407,"text":"these reefs that we dive on\nstart out near the surface"},{"time":532796,"text":"and they go almost vertically,\ncompletely straight down."},{"time":535468,"text":"So we drop in the water\nand go over the edge of this cliff,"},{"time":538373,"text":"and then we start dropping,\ndropping, dropping."},{"time":540611,"text":"People ask if it takes\na long time to get there."},{"time":542945,"text":"No; it only takes a couple minutes\nto get down to three or four hundred feet,"},{"time":546662,"text":"which is what we're aiming for."},{"time":548178,"text":"It's like skydiving in slow motion.\nIt's really very interesting."},{"time":551268,"text":"You ever see \"The Abyss,\""},{"time":552580,"text":"where Ed Harris is sinking down\nalong the side of the wall?"},{"time":555390,"text":"That's what it feels like. Amazing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557137,"text":"And down there, you find that the water\nis very clear, extremely clear,"},{"time":560558,"text":"because there's hardly any plankton."},{"time":562305,"text":"When you turn on your light\nand look around the caves,"},{"time":564866,"text":"you're confronted with a tremendous\namount of diversity,"},{"time":567523,"text":"much more than anyone used to believe."},{"time":569360,"text":"Now, not all of it is new species --"},{"time":571118,"text":"that fish you see with the white stripe,\nthat's a known species."},{"time":574843,"text":"But if you look carefully\ninto the cracks and crevices,"},{"time":578193,"text":"you'll see little things\nscurrying all over the place."},{"time":581297,"text":"There's a just unbelievable diversity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583784,"text":"It's not just fish, either."},{"time":585134,"text":"These are crinoids, sponges, black corals.\nThere're some more fishes."},{"time":588636,"text":"Those fishes that you see now\nare new species."},{"time":590922,"text":"They're still new species,"},{"time":592296,"text":"because I had a video camera\ninstead of my net,"},{"time":594542,"text":"so they're still waiting down there\nfor someone to go find them."},{"time":597609,"text":"But this is what it looks like."},{"time":599153,"text":"And this kind of habitat just goes\non and on and on for miles."},{"time":602311,"text":"This is Papua, New Guinea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604269,"text":"Now little fishes and invertebrates\naren't the only things we see down there."},{"time":608828,"text":"We also see sharks,"},{"time":610126,"text":"much more regularly\nthan I would have expected to."},{"time":612531,"text":"We're not quite sure why."},{"time":613756,"text":"What I want you to do now\nis imagine yourself 400 feet underwater,"},{"time":616889,"text":"with all this high-tech gear on your back,"},{"time":618921,"text":"you're in a remote reef\noff Papua, New Guinea,"},{"time":621093,"text":"thousands of miles from the nearest\nrecompression chamber,"},{"time":623878,"text":"and you're completely\nsurrounded by sharks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626313,"text":"(Video) Diver 1: (In squeaky voice)\nLook at those ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628822,"text":"Diver 2: Uh, oh ..."},{"time":630009,"text":"Uh, oh!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":631184,"text":"Audience: (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":632422,"text":"(Video) Diver 1: I think we have\ntheir attention ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634971,"text":"Richard Pyle: When you start\ntalking like Donald Duck,"},{"time":637525,"text":"there's no situation in the world\nthat can seem tense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640122,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":642080,"text":"So we're down there --\nthis is at 400 feet."},{"time":645018,"text":"That's looking straight up, by the way,\nto give a sense of how far the surface is."},{"time":648916,"text":"And if you're a biologist\nand know about sharks,"},{"time":651188,"text":"and you want to assess,\nhow much jeopardy am I really in here,"},{"time":654462,"text":"there's one question that sort of jumps\nto the forefront of your mind immediately,"},{"time":660374,"text":"which is --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":661554,"text":"(Video) Diver 1: What kind of sharks?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":664030,"text":"Diver 2: Silvertip sharks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665816,"text":"Diver 1: Oh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667006,"text":"RP: There are actually\nthree species of sharks here."},{"time":669527,"text":"The silvertips are the ones\nwith the white edges on the fins,"},{"time":672439,"text":"and there're also gray reef sharks\nand hammerheads off in the distance."},{"time":675947,"text":"And yes, it's a little nerve-racking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679804,"text":"(Video) Diver 2: Hoo!"},{"time":682526,"text":"That little guy is frisky!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":684385,"text":"Audience: (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":687682,"text":"Now, you've seen video like this on TV\na lot, and it's very intimidating."},{"time":692181,"text":"I think it gives the wrong\nimpression about sharks;"},{"time":694598,"text":"they're actually not\nvery dangerous animals."},{"time":696708,"text":"That's why we weren't worried much\nand were joking around."},{"time":699466,"text":"More people are killed\nby pigs, by lightning strikes,"},{"time":702167,"text":"more people are killed\nat soccer games in England."},{"time":704526,"text":"There's a lot of other ways you can die."},{"time":706597,"text":"And I'm not making that stuff up."},{"time":708395,"text":"Coconuts! You can get killed by a coconut\nmore likely than killed by a shark."},{"time":712121,"text":"So sharks aren't quite as dangerous\nas most people make them out to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716122,"text":"Now, I don't know if any of you get\nUS News and World Report --"},{"time":719201,"text":"I got the recent issue."},{"time":720423,"text":"There's a cover story\nabout the great explorers of our time."},{"time":723264,"text":"The last article is entitled,\n\"No New Frontiers.\""},{"time":726988,"text":"It questions whether or not there\nreally are any new frontiers out there,"},{"time":730457,"text":"whether there are any true, hardcore\ndiscoveries that can still be made."},{"time":733885,"text":"My favorite line from the article:"},{"time":735534,"text":"[... 'discovery' can mean finding a guppy\nwith an extra spine in its dorsal fin.\"]"},{"time":739427,"text":"I have to laugh; they don't call us\nfish nerds for nothing."},{"time":742218,"text":"We actually do get excited about finding\na new dorsal spine in a guppy."},{"time":745582,"text":"But it's much more than that."},{"time":747003,"text":"I want to show you a few of the guppies\nwe've found over the years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750603,"text":"This one -- you can see how ugly it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752753,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":753802,"text":"Even if you ignore\nthe scientific value of this thing,"},{"time":756875,"text":"look at the monetary value of this thing."},{"time":758876,"text":"A couple of these were sold\nthrough the aquarium trade to Japan,"},{"time":761953,"text":"where they sold for 15,000 dollars apiece."},{"time":764090,"text":"That's half a million dollars a pound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767325,"text":"Here's another new angelfish\nwe discovered."},{"time":769372,"text":"This one we first discovered back\nin the air days -- the bad old air days,"},{"time":772882,"text":"when we were doing\nthese kind of dives with air."},{"time":775295,"text":"We were at 360 feet."},{"time":776477,"text":"I remember coming up from one\nof these deep dives and I had this fog,"},{"time":779759,"text":"and the narcosis takes a little while\nto fade away, sort of like sobering up."},{"time":784020,"text":"I had this vague recollection of seeing\nthis yellow fish with a black spot,"},{"time":787750,"text":"and thought, \"Damn,\nI should have caught one --"},{"time":790121,"text":"I think that's a new species.\""},{"time":791587,"text":"Eventually, I looked in my bucket."},{"time":793238,"text":"Sure enough, I had caught one,\nI just completely forgot."},{"time":796243,"text":"So this one, we decided to give\nthe name Centropyge narcosis to."},{"time":800121,"text":"That's its official scientific name,"},{"time":802108,"text":"in reference to its deep-dwelling habits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804094,"text":"This is another neat one."},{"time":805311,"text":"When we first found it,"},{"time":806494,"text":"we weren't even sure\nwhat family it belonged to,"},{"time":808777,"text":"so we just called it the Dr. Seuss fish,"},{"time":810714,"text":"since it looked like something\nfrom one of those books."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813316,"text":"Now, this one's pretty cool."},{"time":814690,"text":"If you go to Papua, New Guinea\nand go down 300 feet,"},{"time":817156,"text":"you'll see these big mounds."},{"time":818536,"text":"This may be hard to see,\nbut they're a couple meters in diameter."},{"time":821807,"text":"If you look closely, you'll see\nthere's a little white and gray fish"},{"time":825168,"text":"that hangs out near them."},{"time":826399,"text":"It turns out this little white fish\nbuilds these giant mounds,"},{"time":829434,"text":"one pebble at a time."},{"time":830982,"text":"It's extraordinary\nto find something like this."},{"time":833200,"text":"It's not just new species,\nit's new behaviors, new ecology,"},{"time":835995,"text":"all kind of new things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":837170,"text":"What I'm going to show you now, quickly,"},{"time":839119,"text":"is a sampling of the new species\nwe've discovered."},{"time":841540,"text":"What's extraordinary is not just\nthe number of species we're finding --"},{"time":844921,"text":"though as you can see,\nthat's pretty amazing;"},{"time":847091,"text":"this is only half of what we've found --"},{"time":849028,"text":"what's extraordinary\nis how quickly we find them."},{"time":851948,"text":"We're up to seven new species per hour\nof time we spend at that depth."},{"time":855307,"text":"If you go to an Amazon jungle and fog\na tree, you may get a lot of bugs,"},{"time":859651,"text":"but for fishes,\nthere's nowhere in the world"},{"time":861772,"text":"you can get seven new species\nper hour of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864653,"text":"Now, we've done some\nback-of-the-envelope calculations,"},{"time":867264,"text":"and we're predicting there are probably\nabout 2,000 to 2,500 new species"},{"time":870712,"text":"in the Indo-Pacific alone."},{"time":872085,"text":"There are only five\nto six thousand known species,"},{"time":874763,"text":"so a very large percentage\nof what is out there isn't really known."},{"time":878359,"text":"We thought we had a handle on all the reef\nfish diversity -- evidently not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881963,"text":"I'm going to just close\non a very somber note."},{"time":884209,"text":"At the beginning, I said I'd show you\ntwo extraordinary photographs."},{"time":888193,"text":"This is the second extraordinary\nphotograph I'm going to show you."},{"time":891376,"text":"This one was taken at the exact moment\nI was down there filming those sharks."},{"time":895588,"text":"This was taken exactly\n300 feet above my head."},{"time":899076,"text":"The reason this photograph\nis extraordinary"},{"time":901200,"text":"is because it captures a moment"},{"time":902742,"text":"in the very last minute\nof a person's life."},{"time":905200,"text":"Less than 60 seconds after this picture\nwas taken, this guy was dead."},{"time":909618,"text":"When we recovered his body,\nwe figured out what had gone wrong."},{"time":912805,"text":"He had made a very simple mistake;"},{"time":914469,"text":"he turned the wrong valve\nwhen he filled his cylinder."},{"time":917025,"text":"he had 80 percent oxygen in his tank\nwhen he should have had 40."},{"time":920054,"text":"He had an oxygen toxicity\nseizure and he drowned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922734,"text":"The reason I show this --\nnot to put a downer on everything --"},{"time":925682,"text":"but I just want to use it to key off\nmy philosophy of life in general,"},{"time":929595,"text":"which is that we all have two goals."},{"time":931357,"text":"The first goal we share with every other\nliving thing on this planet,"},{"time":934625,"text":"which is to survive."},{"time":935809,"text":"I call it perpetuation: the survival\nof the species and survival of ourselves,"},{"time":939713,"text":"And those are both\nabout perpetuating the genome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942203,"text":"The second goal, for those of us\nwho have mastered the first goal --"},{"time":945471,"text":"call it spiritual fulfillment,\ncall it financial success,"},{"time":949874,"text":"you can call it any number\nof different things."},{"time":952225,"text":"I call it seeking joy,\nthis pursuit of happiness."},{"time":954934,"text":"So, I guess my theme on this\nis this guy lived his life to the fullest,"},{"time":958597,"text":"he absolutely did."},{"time":959791,"text":"You have to balance those two goals."},{"time":961601,"text":"If you live your whole life in fear --"},{"time":963492,"text":"I mean, life is a sexually transmitted\ndisease with 100 percent mortality."},{"time":968065,"text":"So you can't live your life in fear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970249,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":972493,"text":"I thought that was an old one!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":974761,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":975836,"text":"But at the same time, you don't want\nto get so focused on rule number two,"},{"time":980001,"text":"goal number two,"},{"time":981477,"text":"that you neglect goal number one."},{"time":983200,"text":"Because once you're dead, you really can't\nenjoy anything after that."},{"time":986469,"text":"So I wish you all the best of luck\nin maintaining that balance"},{"time":989469,"text":"in your future endeavors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":990685,"text":"Thanks."}]}]}